title: Esophageal cancer cases in England 2017 , by age and gender
summary: This grouped bar chart represents New registrations on the Y-axis. And, how the value changed throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women.
All through the Months, similar trend was observed for Women and Men. In both cases, the New registrations have increased.
Out of all 2 groups, Men had the highest New registrations in Month 70-74 and Women had the lowest New registrations in Month 20-24.
In Month 70-74, Women had the highest New registrations among all 15 Months and it has the lowest New registrations in Month 20-24.
min_summary: This is a grouped bar chart showing New registrations on the Y-axis throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women on the X-axis.
Over the 15 Months, the New registrations for both Women and Men have increased.

max_summary: This is a grouped bar chart showing New registrations on the Y-axis throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women on the X-axis.
Over the 15 Months, the New registrations for both Women and Men have increased.
Month 70-74 had the maximum New registrations among all 2 groups, and it was for Men. The minimum New registrations was observed in Month 20-24 for Women.
In Month 70-74, Women had the highest New registrations among all 15 Months and it has the lowest New registrations in Month 20-24.
Month 70-74 and 20-24 had the biggest gap of 371.0 between the highest and lowest New registrations found for Women.
Out of all 2 groups, the highest gap between the maximum and minimum New registrations was found in case of Men.
Averaging all 2 groups Men, and Women, the Month 70-74 is the maximum New registrations and 20-24 is the minimum New registrations.
